---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="TypeScript API Conversion - sls.tf Examples">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="docs-header">
      <h1>TypeScript API Conversion Guide</h1>
      <p class="docs-description">
        Complete guide to convert a TypeScript Serverless Framework application to work with sls.tf
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          This guide demonstrates how to convert a production-ready TypeScript Serverless Framework application
          to use sls.tf for Terraform deployment. We'll use the excellent <a href="https://github.com/elastic-coders/serverless-aws-nodejs-typescript-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AWS TypeScript API template</a>
          and <a href="https://blog.logrocket.com/building-serverless-app-typescript/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LogRocket's tutorial</a>
          as our reference implementation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Source Project Analysis</h2>

        <h3>Project Structure</h3>
        <p>The reference project has this structure:</p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Project Directory</h4>
          <pre><code>aws-serverless-typescript-api/
├── src/
│   ├── functions/
│   │   └── todo/
│   │       ├── handler.ts
│   │       └── index.ts
│   ├── libs/
│   │   ├── api-gateway.ts
│   │   ├── handler-resolver.ts
│   │   └── lambda.ts
│   ├── model/
│   │   └── Todo.ts
│   └── services/
│       └── todosService.ts
├── package.json
├── serverless.ts
├── tsconfig.json
└── README.md</code></pre>
        </div>

        <h3>Key Features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>TypeScript Support:</strong> Full TypeScript compilation with type safety</li>
          <li><strong>CRUD API:</strong> Complete Todo API with GET, POST, PUT, DELETE operations</li>
          <li><strong>DynamoDB Integration:</strong> Serverless-managed DynamoDB table</li>
          <li><strong>Middleware:</strong> Middy.js middleware for request processing</li>
          <li><strong>Local Development:</strong> serverless-offline and DynamoDB local for testing</li>
          <li><strong>ESBuild:</strong> Fast bundling and deployment</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Conversion Plan</h2>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h3>Phase 1: Project Setup</h3>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Add sls.tf Module:</strong> Add sls.tf as a Git submodule to the project</li>
            <li><strong>Initialize Terraform:</strong> Set up Terraform configuration files</li>
            <li><strong>Update Dependencies:</strong> Ensure compatibility with sls.tf requirements</li>
            <li><strong>Configure Path Resolution:</strong> Set up proper module paths</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h3>Phase 2: Configuration Conversion</h3>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Update serverless.ts:</strong> Ensure sls.tf compatibility</li>
            <li><strong>Add Environment Variables:</strong> Configure Terraform-specific variables</li>
            <li><strong>Update IAM Roles:</strong> Let sls.tf manage IAM permissions</li>
            <li><strong>Adjust Build Configuration:</strong> Optimize for Terraform deployment</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h3>Phase 3: Terraform Configuration</h3>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Create main.tf:</strong> Basic Terraform configuration</li>
            <li><strong>Configure Variables:</strong> Set up input variables for customization</li>
            <li><strong>Configure Outputs:</strong> Export important resource outputs</li>
            <li><strong>Set Up Environment:</strong> Configure staging/production environments</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h3>Phase 4: Deployment & Testing</h3>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Local Testing:</strong> Verify functionality with sls.tf locally</li>
            <li><strong>Infrastructure Planning:</strong> Review Terraform execution plan</li>
            <li><strong>Deploy Infrastructure:</strong> Apply Terraform configuration</li>
            <li><strong>API Testing:</strong> Verify all endpoints work correctly</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Detailed Implementation Steps</h2>

        <h3>Step 1: Install sls.tf as Hybrid Module</h3>
        <p>
          sls.tf works as both a Terraform module AND an NPM package. This hybrid approach ensures
          full TypeScript parsing capabilities while keeping everything in sync.
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Install sls.tf locally for TypeScript parsing</h4>
          <pre><code># Navigate to your project root
cd /path/to/your-project

# Install sls.tf from Git repository for TypeScript parsing
npm install https://github.com/sls-tf/sls.tf.git

# Create main.tf for Terraform configuration
touch main.tf

# Create variables.tf for input variables
touch variables.tf

# Create outputs.tf for resource outputs
touch outputs.tf</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h4>Current Reality: Git-Based Installation</h4>
          <p><strong>Two installations, one source - both from the same GitHub repository:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Terraform Module:</strong> <code>source = "github.com/sls-tf/sls.tf"</code> (downloaded during <code>terraform init</code>)</li>
            <li><strong>NPM Package:</strong> <code>npm install https://github.com/sls-tf/sls.tf.git</code> (for TypeScript parser)</li>
            <li><strong>Automatic Integration:</strong> Terraform automatically finds the locally installed parser</li>
            <li><strong>Version Consistency:</strong> Both use the same Git commit, so versions stay in sync</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Dual Installation Example</h4>
          <pre><code># Terminal session showing both installations
cd /path/to/your-project

# 1. Install as NPM package (gets TypeScript parser with dependencies)
npm install https://github.com/sls-tf/sls.tf.git

# 2. Configure Terraform (downloads same repo as module)
cat > main.tf << 'EOF'
module "serverless_api" {
  source = "github.com/sls-tf/sls.tf"
  config_path = "${path.root}/serverless.ts"
  config_format = "typescript"
}
EOF

# 3. Terraform finds both installations automatically
terraform init
# ✅ Downloads Terraform module from GitHub
# ✅ Detects local NPM installation of TypeScript parser
# ✅ TypeScript parsing works!</code></pre>
        </div>

        <h3>Step 2: Configure serverless.ts for sls.tf</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>With the hybrid approach, you can keep your original serverless.ts file!</strong>
          Only minor adjustments are needed for sls.tf compatibility:
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Updated serverless.ts (minimal changes)</h4>
          <pre><code>import type { AWS } from '@serverless/typescript';
import { createTodo, getTodo, getAllTodos, updateTodo, deleteTodo } from '@functions/todo';

const serverlessConfiguration: AWS = {
  service: 'aws-serverless-typescript-api',
  frameworkVersion: '3',

  // Remove plugins that sls.tf handles differently
  // Keep only essential plugins
  plugins: ['serverless-esbuild'],

  provider: {
    name: 'aws',
    runtime: 'nodejs18.x',  // Updated runtime
    apiGateway: {
      minimumCompressionSize: 1024,
      shouldStartNameWithService: true,
    },
    environment: {
      AWS_NODEJS_CONNECTION_REUSE_ENABLED: '1',
      NODE_OPTIONS: '--enable-source-maps --stack-trace-limit=1000',
      // Add sls.tf specific variables
      TABLE_NAME: '${self:custom.tableName}',
      REGION: '${opt:region, self:provider.region}',
    },
    // Let sls.tf manage IAM roles automatically
    // iam: { ... } // Remove this section
  },

  // Functions remain exactly the same!
  functions: { getAllTodos, createTodo, getTodo, updateTodo, deleteTodo },

  package: {
    individually: true,
    exclude: ['node_modules/**']
  },

  custom: {
    esbuild: {
      bundle: true,
      minify: false,
      sourcemap: true,
      exclude: ['aws-sdk'],
      target: 'node18',
      define: { 'require.resolve': undefined },
      platform: 'node',
      concurrency: 10,
    },
    // Custom properties for sls.tf
    tableName: '${sls:customTableName}',
  },

  // Remove DynamoDB from CloudFormation - sls.tf will create it
  // resources: { ... } // Remove this section
};

export default serverlessConfiguration;</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h4>Key Changes for sls.tf Compatibility</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Remove Development Plugins:</strong> serverless-offline, serverless-dynamodb-local</li>
            <li><strong>Remove IAM Configuration:</strong> Let sls.tf manage roles automatically</li>
            <li><strong>Remove CloudFormation Resources:</strong> sls.tf creates these as native Terraform</li>
            <li><strong>Keep Everything Else:</strong> Functions, handlers, and build configuration stay the same</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3>Step 3: Create Terraform Configuration</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>main.tf</h4>
          <pre><code>terraform {'{'}
  required_version = ">= 1.0"
  required_providers {'{'}
    aws = {'{'}
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    {'}'}
  {'}'}
{'}'}

provider "aws" {'{'}
  region = var.aws_region
{'}'}

# Reference the existing serverless configuration
module "serverless_api" {'{'}
  source = "github.com/sls-tf/sls.tf"

  # Required variables
  config_path    = "${path.root}/serverless.ts"
  config_format  = "typescript"  # ✅ Full TypeScript support!
  aws_region     = var.aws_region

  # Optional variables
  lambda_code_path = "."
{'}'}

# Outputs
output "api_gateway_invoke_url" {'{'}
  description = "API Gateway invoke URL"
  value       = module.serverless_api.api_gateway_invoke_url
{'}'}

output "function_names" {'{'}
  description = "Lambda function names"
  value       = module.serverless_api.function_names
{'}'}

output "function_arns" {'{'}
  description = "Lambda function ARNs"
  value       = module.serverless_api.function_arns
{'}'}

output "service_name" {'{'}
  description = "Serverless service name"
  value       = module.serverless_api.service_name
{'}'}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>variables.tf</h4>
          <pre><code>variable "aws_region" {'{'}
  description = "AWS region for deployment"
  type        = string
  default     = "us-east-1"
{'}'}

variable "environment" {'{'}
  description = "Environment name (dev, staging, production)"
  type        = string
  default     = "dev"
{'}'}

variable "resource_prefix" {'{'}
  description = "Prefix for resource names"
  type        = string
  default     = "serverless-api"
{'}'}

variable "tags" {'{'}
  description = "Tags to apply to all resources"
  type        = map(string)
  default = {'{'}
    Project     = "Serverless TypeScript API"
    Environment = "development"
    ManagedBy   = "sls.tf"
  {'}'}
{'}'}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Migration Considerations</h2>

        <h3>Build Process Changes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>ESBuild vs sls.tf:</strong> sls.tf handles the build process differently</li>
          <li><strong>Package Management:</strong> Adjust package exclusions for optimal deployment</li>
          <li><strong>File Structure:</strong> Ensure proper path resolution for imports</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Configuration Adjustments</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Plugin Removal:</strong> Remove serverless-offline and dynamodb-local plugins</li>
          <li><strong>IAM Management:</strong> Let sls.tf create and manage IAM roles</li>
          <li><strong>Resource Separation:</strong> Move CloudFormation resources to Terraform</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Development Workflow</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Local Development:</strong> Continue using serverless-offline for local testing</li>
          <li><strong>Infrastructure Testing:</strong> Use Terraform plan and validate</li>
          <li><strong>CI/CD Integration:</strong> Update deployment pipelines for Terraform</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Testing Strategy</h2>

        <h3>Local Testing</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Continue using Serverless Framework locally</h4>
          <pre><code># Install dependencies
npm install

# Start local development
npm run dev

# Test functions locally
npx sls invoke local -f getAllTodos</code></pre>
        </div>

        <h3>Step 4: Test Hybrid Installation</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Test TypeScript parsing and Terraform configuration</h4>
          <pre><code># Navigate to project root
cd /path/to/your-project

# Verify sls.tf NPM installation
ls node_modules/sls-tf/
# Should show: scripts/, package.json, etc.

# Initialize Terraform (will auto-download module)
terraform init
# ✅ Terraform will find the locally installed TypeScript parser!

# Validate configuration (includes TypeScript parsing)
terraform validate

# Plan deployment (TypeScript config parsed automatically)
terraform plan

# Apply changes when ready
terraform apply</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="plan-section">
          <h4>What Happens During terraform init</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Module Download:</strong> Downloads sls.tf Terraform module from GitHub</li>
            <li><strong>Parser Detection:</strong> Detects local NPM installation of sls-tf</li>
            <li><strong>TypeScript Ready:</strong> TypeScript parser found with all dependencies</li>
            <li><strong>Configuration Parse:</strong> serverless.ts parsed automatically during plan</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3>Integration Testing</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Test deployed API</h4>
          <pre><code># Get API endpoint from Terraform output
API_URL=$(terraform output -raw api_gateway_url)

# Test GET all todos
curl -X GET "$API_URL/todo/"

# Test POST new todo
curl -X POST "$API_URL/todo" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title": "Test Todo from sls.tf", "completed": false}'

# Test GET specific todo
curl -X GET "$API_URL/todo/{id}"</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Benefits of sls.tf Migration</h2>

        <div class="benefits-grid">
          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>🔒 Infrastructure as Code</h3>
            <p>All AWS resources managed through Terraform with proper state tracking</p>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>🚀 Production Ready</h3>
            <p>Built-in security, monitoring, and disaster recovery capabilities</p>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>🔄 Improved Workflow</h3>
            <p>Standardized deployment process with proper planning and validation</p>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>📊 Better Observability</h3>
            <p>Centralized resource management and monitoring</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

        <h3>Common Issues</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Import Resolution:</strong> Ensure TypeScript path resolution works correctly</li>
          <li><strong>Build Errors:</strong> Check ESBuild configuration compatibility</li>
          <li><strong>Resource Conflicts:</strong> Use unique resource names to avoid conflicts</li>
          <li><strong>Permission Issues:</strong> Verify IAM roles have necessary permissions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Migration Tips</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Gradual Migration:</strong> Consider migrating one service at a time</li>
          <li><strong>Backup Configuration:</strong> Keep original serverless.yml as reference</li>
          <li><strong>Test Thoroughly:</strong> Test all functionality before production deployment</li>
          <li><strong>Monitor Costs:</strong> Track resource usage and costs after migration</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>

        <p>After completing this migration:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Set up CI/CD pipelines for automated deployment</li>
          <li>Configure monitoring and alerting</li>
          <li>Implement proper logging and error handling</li>
          <li>Add automated testing to the deployment pipeline</li>
          <li>Document your sls.tf configuration for team members</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>References</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/elastic-coders/serverless-aws-nodejs-typescript-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Original TypeScript Template</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://blog.logrocket.com/building-serverless-app-typescript/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LogRocket TypeScript Tutorial</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/features/typescript">TypeScript Support in sls.tf</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/configuration">Advanced Configuration Guide</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

